  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Red Cross focusses on national- and international aid, aiming to relieve the immense pressure on the health care systems and striving to ensure that everyone receives the medical attention that they need wherever and whenever necessary, so also during the corona crisis.
The Red Cross has two main objectives:
1. To support and enhance health care centres, doctors&#x2019; practices and hospitals by offering them a helping hand, providing logistical support and by sharing knowledge and resources. This gives them more time with their patients and gives them the opportunity to help more people in need.
2. To fight the rise of the coronavirus and to cut down the number of infections, thereby reducing the number of patients in need of medical attention.</narrative>
  </description>
